The '''Institute for Therapy through the Art''' is a [[non-profit]] [[Creative arts therapies|creative arts therapy]] organization in [[Evanston, Illinois]], in the United States.<ref>{{cite web |title=Profile: Institute for Therapy through the Arts |url=https://projects.propublica.org/nonprofits/organizations/473047364 |publisher=Nonprofit Explorer - ProPublica |accessdate=14 November 2018 |language=en}}</ref> It was founded in 1975 by Marilyn Richman, a [[drama therapist]], as a division of the [[Music Institute of Chicago]], with the help of [[Frank Little (tenor)|Frank Little]], the director at the time.<ref name=Trib2015>{{cite news |last1=Ingram |first1=Bruce |title=Institute for Therapy through Arts marks 40 years |url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/suburbs/evanston/news/ct-evr-trend-therapyaward-tl-0528-20150519-story.html |work=Pioneer Press via The Chicago Tribune |date=May 19, 2015}}</ref><ref name=NYT>{{cite news |last1=Midgette |first1=Anne |title=Frank Little, 69, Met Tenor and Educator, Dies |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/03/06/obituaries/frank-little-69-met-tenor-and-educator-dies.html |work=The New York Times |date=March 6, 2006 |language=en}}</ref>

